{
  "title": "Amazon Aurora DSQL CDC to Amazon EventBridge Fan-out",
  "description": "Stream real-time database changes from Amazon Aurora DSQL via CDC to Amazon EventBridge for content-based routing to multiple consumers",
  "language": "TypeScript",
  "level": "300",
  "framework": "AWS CDK",
  "introBox": {
    "headline": "How it works",
    "text": [
      "Amazon Aurora DSQL captures committed row-level changes (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) and streams them as JSON records to Amazon Kinesis Data Streams.",
      "AWS Lambda consumes the stream, classifies each CDC event by operation type, and publishes typed events to an Amazon EventBridge custom event bus.",
      "Amazon EventBridge routes events to three independent consumers: Amazon SQS (audit trail for ALL events), AWS Step Functions (validation workflow for INSERTs), and Amazon SNS (alerting for DELETEs)."
    ]
  },
